      • associationValid

        public static boolean associationValid​(RegulatoryGraph regGraph,
                                       DynamicGraph dynGraph)
        Test if an association between a regulatory graph and a state transition graph is valid: all what we can do is checking the node-order to see if they obviously differ (by size of node's name). if this function returns true, it's _NOT_ a garanty that both graphs are compatibles, for exemple the state transition graph could have higher max value for one of the node.
        Parameters:
        regGraph -
        dynGraph -
        Returns:
        true if the two graph can be associated
